<div id="review_2067627060" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2067627060" />
    <a title="W" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49365462-w"><img alt="W" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610208667p2/49365462.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2067627060?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="W" class="user" itemprop="url" name="W" href="/user/show/49365462-w">W</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49365462-w?shelf=misc">misc</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2067627060" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12449872839320176166">October 8,2005,a day that remains etched in memory.A killer earthquake struck Pakistan and left unprecedented devastation in its wake.<br/>I was not in Pakistan,however,when it happened.<br/><br/>But in subsequent years,I have experienced some of the scariest earthquakes imaginable.Luckily,the destruction was not as extreme.<br/><br/>Greg Mortensen (of the controversial Three Cups of Tea fame) is the author of this book too.Allegations of fabrications,funds embezzlement and the suicide of his co-author have dented his c</span>
  <span id="freeText12449872839320176166" style="display:none">October 8,2005,a day that remains etched in memory.A killer earthquake struck Pakistan and left unprecedented devastation in its wake.<br />I was not in Pakistan,however,when it happened.<br /><br />But in subsequent years,I have experienced some of the scariest earthquakes imaginable.Luckily,the destruction was not as extreme.<br /><br />Greg Mortensen (of the controversial Three Cups of Tea fame) is the author of this book too.Allegations of fabrications,funds embezzlement and the suicide of his co-author have dented his credibility.<br /><br />Still,he wrote this sequel to Three Cups of Tea.He is the do gooder wanting to build and re build schools in the remote areas of Pakistan and Afghanistan.<br /><br />This book is not easy to read as it goes into the details of what happened on that unfortunate day,how the earth shook with a terrible roar and everyone thought that qayamat (the end of the world) had arrived.Pakistan's Azad Kashmir bore the brunt of the earthquake.<br /><br />It is difficult to read because of the account of the sufferings of the victims.It is debatable how much good work he actually did,following the controversy ignited by his previous book.<br /><br />Of course,he gives lots of details about how he helped out.Can't accept his account at face value anymore.<br /><br />But I still hope he helped out,as the victims of this earthquake needed all the help they could get.<br /><br />Postscript : Years after the earthquake,newspapers continue to report on the anniversaries of the quake,that the victims have not been rehabilitated or properly compensated.The government quietly diverted the money meant for reconstruction to some other purpose ! No surprises there.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12449872839320176166" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


