    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_215694739" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/215694739" />
    <a title="Audrey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6007245-audrey"><img alt="Audrey" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1386729720p2/6007245.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/215694739?book_show_action=true">Feb 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Audrey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Audrey" href="/user/show/6007245-audrey">Audrey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6007245-audrey?shelf=asia">asia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6007245-audrey?shelf=travel">travel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6007245-audrey?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6007245-audrey?shelf=biographies-and-memoirs">biographies-and-memoirs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer215694739" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14731350606432425824">Greg Mortenson continues his story that was started in Three Cups of Tea. The organization he founded, Central Asia Institute, is a strong promoter of women&apos;s education in Pakistan and Afghanistan. He discusses the dangers they face in building schools in the remotest parts of the countries. He talks about the history and culture of those countries and the many challenges that they face. One particularly heartbreaking was the major earthquake in Pakistan in 2005. Building relationships with thos</span>
  <span id="freeText14731350606432425824" style="display:none">Greg Mortenson continues his story that was started in Three Cups of Tea. The organization he founded, Central Asia Institute, is a strong promoter of women's education in Pakistan and Afghanistan. He discusses the dangers they face in building schools in the remotest parts of the countries. He talks about the history and culture of those countries and the many challenges that they face. One particularly heartbreaking was the major earthquake in Pakistan in 2005. Building relationships with those of different cultures is a terrific way to build peace between nations. Promoting literacy, especially among women, is great way to improve the lives of community. It is so much better solve problems this way than through war. This book was well worth listening to.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14731350606432425824" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
